01:46:28,924 --> 01:46:31,884
Yeah, but you can really see 'em
if you want to, can't you?

1017
01:46:31,968 --> 01:46:34,970
I mean, you can go home with 'em
if you want to. All these places say that.

1018
01:46:35,055 --> 01:46:39,558
How much extra money do you make? How much -
How much money do you make on the side?

1019
01:46:51,071 --> 01:46:55,533
I'm sorry, sir. I think you'll maybe
want to talk to one of the other girls.

1020
01:46:55,617 --> 01:46:57,910
I'll see if I can find one for you.

1021
01:46:57,994 --> 01:47:00,454
No. No, no, no!

1022
01:47:00,539 --> 01:47:02,540
Please. Please.

1023
01:47:04,126 --> 01:47:06,127
Please don't go.

1024
01:47:10,674 --> 01:47:13,926
I just don't think
I'm the one you want to talk to.

1025
01:47:16,346 --> 01:47:18,722
Please.

1026
01:47:18,807 --> 01:47:21,142
Please don't go. I'm sorry.

1027
01:47:29,818 --> 01:47:32,361
All right.

1028
01:47:38,034 --> 01:47:42,496
I'm, um - I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1029
01:47:47,419 --> 01:47:50,463
That's okay.

1030
01:47:58,847 --> 01:48:00,848
You know, I -

1031
01:48:00,932 --> 01:48:04,435
I know how hard it is to talk
to strangers sometimes.

1032
01:48:09,733 --> 01:48:11,692
Just relax.

1033
01:48:13,153 --> 01:48:15,571
Relax and tell me what's on your mind.

1034
01:48:17,908 --> 01:48:19,867
I'll listen...

1035
01:48:21,912 --> 01:48:23,871
to you.

1036
01:48:28,376 --> 01:48:30,878
I don't mind listening.

1037
01:48:38,762 --> 01:48:41,430
I do it all the time.

1038
01:49:02,494 --> 01:49:04,745
She was there, wasn't she?

1039
01:49:43,243 --> 01:49:45,160
What's that?

1040
01:49:50,625 --> 01:49:52,543
A vacant lot.

1041
01:49:52,627 --> 01:49:57,298
I bought that land when we were all together,
with your mom.

1042
01:50:00,302 --> 01:50:03,304
I thought we might live there someday.

1043
01:50:05,682 --> 01:50:07,391
Where?

1044
01:50:07,475 --> 01:50:10,686
Paris, Texas.

1045
01:50:10,770 --> 01:50:12,688
Where's that?

1046
01:50:14,024 --> 01:50:16,692
It's close to the Red River.

1047
01:50:21,072 --> 01:50:23,449
Do you like it?

1048
01:50:23,533 --> 01:50:26,118
You mean we'd live on dirt?

1049
01:50:41,259 --> 01:50:44,261
Why do you drink that stuff?
It stinks.

1050
01:50:46,222 --> 01:50:49,725
- Wait a minute. Where are you going?
- To the truck.

1051
01:51:10,413 --> 01:51:12,414
Have another one?

1052
01:51:53,373 --> 01:51:55,290
Come on, Dad.

1053
01:52:21,025 --> 01:52:23,861
This is not a place to bring a fancy woman.

1054
01:52:26,948 --> 01:52:31,744
Would you say? If you had a fancy woman,
would you bring her in a place like this?

1055
01:52:31,828 --> 01:52:34,288
What's a fancy woman?

1056
01:52:51,097 --> 01:52:54,308
Oh! God.

1057
01:52:54,392 --> 01:52:56,602
My mother -

1058
01:52:57,937 --> 01:52:59,855
Not your mother...

1059
01:52:59,939 --> 01:53:02,608
but my mother...

1060
01:53:02,692 --> 01:53:05,277
was not a fancy woman.

1061
01:53:05,361 --> 01:53:07,780
She was -

1062
01:53:13,161 --> 01:53:17,790
She never wanted to be a fancy woman.
She never even pretended to be a fancy woman.

1063
01:53:17,874 --> 01:53:20,626
Then what was she?

1064
01:53:20,710 --> 01:53:23,253
She was just plain.

1065
01:53:25,507 --> 01:53:27,466
Just plain and good.

1066
01:53:27,550 --> 01:53:30,427
She was very good.

1067
01:53:30,512 --> 01:53:32,429
But my daddy -

1068
01:53:35,016 --> 01:53:37,893
See, my daddy had, uh -

1069
01:53:37,977 --> 01:53:39,978
He had this idea -

1070
01:53:40,063 --> 01:53:44,191
he had this idea in his head
that was kind of-

1071
01:53:44,275 --> 01:53:48,111
kind of-kind of a sickness.

1072
01:53:48,196 --> 01:53:50,113
What idea?

1073
01:53:50,198 --> 01:53:52,658
He had this idea about her...

1074
01:53:52,742 --> 01:53:54,660
and...

1075
01:53:56,120 --> 01:53:58,831
he looked at her...

1076
01:53:58,915 --> 01:54:01,416
but he didn't see her.

1077
01:54:03,920 --> 01:54:07,589
He - He saw this idea.

1078
01:54:11,427 --> 01:54:15,305
And he told people that she was from Paris.

1079
01:54:16,933 --> 01:54:19,685
It was a big joke...

1080
01:54:19,769 --> 01:54:21,687
but he started telling everybody
all the time...

1081
01:54:21,771 --> 01:54:23,772
and finally it wasn't a joke anymore.
He st -

1082
01:54:27,277 --> 01:54:29,444
He started believing it.

1083
01:54:30,864 --> 01:54:34,032
And he actually believed it.

1084
01:54:37,287 --> 01:54:39,371
And she -

1085
01:54:39,455 --> 01:54:41,790
Oh, God.

1086
01:54:41,875 --> 01:54:44,710
She would get so embarrassed.

1087
01:54:46,462 --> 01:54:48,505
She -

1088
01:54:48,590 --> 01:54:50,924
She was so -

1089
01:54:53,094 --> 01:54:55,429
She was so shy.

1090
01:55:43,978 --> 01:55:45,979
Vámonos, muchacho.

1091
01:56:14,801 --> 01:56:16,718
Left, Dad.

1092
01:56:31,401 --> 01:56:33,735
Hunter, it's me.

1093
01:56:36,906 --> 01:56:40,409
I was afraid I'd never be able
to say the right words to you...

1094
01:56:40,493 --> 01:56:42,786
in person...

1095
01:56:42,870 --> 01:56:46,832
so I'm trying to do it like this.

1096
01:56:49,794 --> 01:56:52,921
When I first saw you this time...

1097
01:56:53,923 --> 01:56:55,882
at Walt's...

1098
01:56:57,176 --> 01:57:00,679
I was hoping for all kinds of things.

1099
01:57:02,598 --> 01:57:06,268
I was hoping to show you
that I was your father.

1100
01:57:08,354 --> 01:57:10,522
You showed me I was.

1101
01:57:14,027 --> 01:57:17,029
But the biggest thing I hoped for...

1102
01:57:19,198 --> 01:57:21,199
can't come true.

1103
01:57:23,536 --> 01:57:26,038
I know that now.

1104
01:57:27,707 --> 01:57:30,208
You belong together with your mother.

1105
01:57:32,545 --> 01:57:35,338
You belong together with your mother.

1106
01:57:36,966 --> 01:57:40,135
It was me that tore you apart...

1107
01:57:40,219 --> 01:57:43,722
and I owe it to you to bring you back together.

1108
01:57:45,141 --> 01:57:47,684
But I can't stay with you.

1109
01:57:47,769 --> 01:57:51,354
I could never heal up what happened.

1110
01:57:51,439 --> 01:57:54,900
That's just the way it is.

1111
01:57:54,984 --> 01:57:58,361
I can't even hardly remember what happened.

1112
01:57:58,446 --> 01:58:00,822
It's like a gap.

1113
01:58:00,907 --> 01:58:03,617
But it left me alone in a way that...

1114
01:58:03,701 --> 01:58:06,078
I haven't gotten over.

1115
01:58:06,162 --> 01:58:09,748
And right now, I'm afraid.

1116
01:58:11,459 --> 01:58:14,586
I'm afraid of walking away again.

1117
01:58:14,670 --> 01:58:17,172
I'm afraid of what I might find.

1118
01:58:18,674 --> 01:58:21,384
But I'm even more afraid of...

1119
01:58:21,469 --> 01:58:24,763
not facing this fear.

1120
01:58:24,847 --> 01:58:27,349
I love you, Hunter.

1121
01:58:28,518 --> 01:58:31,269
I love you more than my life.

1122
01:58:42,281 --> 01:58:46,201
Hey.

1123
01:58:50,706 --> 01:58:53,458
Can I tell you something?

1124
01:58:55,002 --> 01:58:57,712
Sure. Anything you like.

1125
01:58:59,215 --> 01:59:01,174
It's kind of long.

1126
01:59:02,218 --> 01:59:04,553
I got plenty of time.

1127
01:59:27,952 --> 01:59:30,328
I knew these people.

1128
01:59:30,413 --> 01:59:32,372
What people?

1129
01:59:33,624 --> 01:59:35,625
These two people.

1130
01:59:40,715 --> 01:59:43,216
They were in love with each other.

1131
01:59:45,720 --> 01:59:48,430
The girl was... very young...

1132
01:59:48,514 --> 01:59:52,184
about 17 or 18, I guess.

1133
01:59:53,603 --> 01:59:57,105
And the guy was... quite a bit older.

1134
01:59:58,649 --> 02:00:01,776
He was kind of raggedy and wild.

1135
02:00:02,904 --> 02:00:05,363
And she was very beautiful, you know?

1136
02:00:07,366 --> 02:00:09,284
Yeah.

1137
02:00:09,368 --> 02:00:13,538
And together they turned everything
into a kind of an adventure...

1138
02:00:14,790 --> 02:00:17,709
and she liked that.

1139
02:00:17,793 --> 02:00:21,588
Just an ordinary trip
down to the grocery store was...

1140
02:00:21,672 --> 02:00:24,716
full of adventure.

1141
02:00:24,800 --> 02:00:28,553
And they were always laughing
at stupid things.

1142
02:00:28,638 --> 02:00:31,765
He liked to make her laugh.

1143
02:00:31,849 --> 02:00:33,850
And...

1144
02:00:35,394 --> 02:00:38,104
they didn't much care for anything else...

1145
02:00:38,189 --> 02:00:42,108
because all they wanted to do
was be with each other.

1146
02:00:43,861 --> 02:00:46,363
They were always together.

1147
02:00:46,447 --> 02:00:49,074
Sounds like they were very happy.

1148
02:00:49,158 --> 02:00:51,993
Yes, they were.

1149
02:00:52,078 --> 02:00:54,913
They were real happy.

1150
02:00:54,997 --> 02:00:58,333
And he - he loved her more than...

1151
02:01:00,836 --> 02:01:03,004
he ever felt possible.

1152
02:01:06,008 --> 02:01:10,595
He couldn't stand being away from her,
uh, during the day when he went to work.

1153
02:01:16,018 --> 02:01:19,020
So he quit...

1154
02:01:19,105 --> 02:01:21,773
just to be home with her.

1155
02:01:21,857 --> 02:01:25,986
Then he'd get anotherjob
when the money ran out...

1156
02:01:26,070 --> 02:01:28,613
and then he'd quit again.

1157
02:01:28,698 --> 02:01:31,533
But pretty soon, she started to worry.

1158
02:01:35,913 --> 02:01:38,748
- About what?
- Money, I guess.

1159
02:01:38,833 --> 02:01:40,750
- Not having enough.
- Mmm.

1160
02:01:40,835 --> 02:01:43,211
Not knowing
when the next check was coming in.

1161
02:01:45,339 --> 02:01:48,133
Yep, I know that feeling.

1162
02:01:48,217 --> 02:01:52,971
So he started to get kind of torn inside.

1163
02:01:56,642 --> 02:01:59,019
How do you mean?

1164
02:01:59,103 --> 02:02:02,188
Well, he knew he had to work to support her...

1165
02:02:02,273 --> 02:02:05,275
but he couldn't stand
being away from her either.

1166
02:02:06,944 --> 02:02:08,862
I see.

1167
02:02:08,946 --> 02:02:12,449
And the more he was away from her,
the crazier he got...

1168
02:02:13,576 --> 02:02:16,578
except now he got really crazy.

1169
02:02:20,041 --> 02:02:22,584
He started imagining all kinds of things.

1170
02:02:24,337 --> 02:02:26,254
Like what?

1171
02:02:27,923 --> 02:02:32,135
He started thinking
that she was seeing other men on the sly.

1172
02:02:33,471 --> 02:02:36,306
He'd come home from work
and accuse her of...

1173
02:02:36,390 --> 02:02:38,850
spending the day with somebody else.

1174
02:02:38,934 --> 02:02:41,686
He'd yell at her and break things in the trailer.

1175
02:02:44,190 --> 02:02:46,107
The trailer.

1176
02:02:51,280 --> 02:02:53,698
Yes.

1177
02:02:53,783 --> 02:02:56,284
They lived in a trailer home.

1178
02:03:11,050 --> 02:03:15,178
Excuse me, sir,
but were you in to visit me the other day?

1179
02:03:15,262 --> 02:03:17,597
I don't mean to pry.

1180
02:03:19,308 --> 02:03:21,893
No.

1181
02:03:21,977 --> 02:03:23,895
Oh.

1182
02:03:25,356 --> 02:03:29,025
I thought I recognized your voice for a minute.

1183
02:03:30,486 --> 02:03:33,488
No. Wasn't me.

1184
02:03:34,865 --> 02:03:36,825
Mm-hmm.

1185
02:03:38,828 --> 02:03:40,829
Please go on.

1186
02:03:43,249 --> 02:03:47,585
Anyway, he started to drink real bad...

1187
02:03:47,670 --> 02:03:50,839
and he'd stay out late to test her.

1188
02:03:52,675 --> 02:03:55,552
What do you mean "test her"?

1189
02:03:55,636 --> 02:03:58,304
To see if she'd get jealous.

1190
02:03:59,306 --> 02:04:01,975
Mm-hmm.

1191
02:04:03,727 --> 02:04:07,564
He wanted her to get jealous, but she didn't.

1192
02:04:07,648 --> 02:04:10,066
She just worried about him...

1193
02:04:10,151 --> 02:04:12,652
but that got him even madder.

1194
02:04:13,863 --> 02:04:16,281
Why?

1195
02:04:16,365 --> 02:04:18,700
Because...

1196
02:04:18,784 --> 02:04:22,203
he thought if she never got jealous of him
that she didn't really care about him.

1197
02:04:23,873 --> 02:04:28,293
Jealousy was a sign of her love for him.

1198
02:04:28,377 --> 02:04:30,795
And then one night -

1199
02:04:30,880 --> 02:04:35,008
one night she told him that she was pregnant.

1200
02:04:35,092 --> 02:04:37,969
She was about three or four months' pregnant...

1201
02:04:38,053 --> 02:04:40,305
and he didn't even know.

1202
02:04:40,389 --> 02:04:43,641
And then suddenly everything changed.

1203
02:04:43,726 --> 02:04:47,687
He stopped drinking and got a steadyjob.

1204
02:04:47,771 --> 02:04:52,734
He was convinced that she loved him now
because she was carrying his child.

1205
02:04:52,818 --> 02:04:56,779
And he was going to dedicate himself
to making a home for her.

1206
02:04:57,948 --> 02:05:00,658
But a funny thing started to happen.

1207
02:05:00,743 --> 02:05:02,368
What?

1208
02:05:02,453 --> 02:05:04,871
He didn't even notice it at first.

1209
02:05:04,955 --> 02:05:07,582
She started to change.

1210
02:05:07,666 --> 02:05:12,587
From the day the baby was born, she began
to get irritated with everything around her.

1211
02:05:12,671 --> 02:05:15,423
She got mad at everything.

1212
02:05:15,508 --> 02:05:19,010
Even the baby seemed to be an injustice to her.

1213
02:05:19,094 --> 02:05:22,055
He kept trying
to make everything all right for her -

1214
02:05:22,139 --> 02:05:26,476
buy her things,
take her out to dinner once a week.

1215
02:05:26,560 --> 02:05:29,312
But nothing seemed to satisfy her.

1216
02:05:29,396 --> 02:05:33,066
For two years,
he struggled to pull them back together...

1217
02:05:33,150 --> 02:05:36,528
like they were when they first met...

1218
02:05:36,612 --> 02:05:41,115
but finally he knew
that it was never gonna work out.

1219
02:05:42,535 --> 02:05:44,661
So he hit the bottle again.

1220
02:05:44,745 --> 02:05:47,789
But this time, it got mean.

1221
02:05:47,873 --> 02:05:50,416
This time, when he came home late at night...

1222
02:05:50,501 --> 02:05:53,836
she wasn't worried about him orjealous.

1223
02:05:53,921 --> 02:05:56,297
She was just enraged.

1224
02:05:57,800 --> 02:06:02,220
She accused him of holding her captive
by making her have a baby.

1225
02:06:04,139 --> 02:06:07,100
She told him that she dreamed about escaping.

1226
02:06:07,184 --> 02:06:11,062
That was all she dreamed about - escape.

1227
02:06:11,146 --> 02:06:15,024
She saw herself at night,
running naked down a highway...

1228
02:06:15,109 --> 02:06:17,235
running across fields...

1229
02:06:17,319 --> 02:06:19,279
running down riverbeds.

1230
02:06:19,363 --> 02:06:21,281
Always running.

1231
02:06:21,365 --> 02:06:25,702
And always, just when she was
about to get away, he'd be there.

1232
02:06:25,786 --> 02:06:29,080
He would stop her somehow.

1233
02:06:29,164 --> 02:06:31,833
He would just appear and stop her.

1234
02:06:34,712 --> 02:06:39,257
And when she told him these dreams,
he believed them.

1235
02:06:39,341 --> 02:06:43,177
He knew she had to be stopped,
or she'd leave him forever.

1236
02:06:43,262 --> 02:06:45,930
So he tied a cowbell to her ankle...

1237
02:06:46,015 --> 02:06:50,018
so he could hear at night
if she tried to get out of bed.

1238
02:06:50,102 --> 02:06:53,980
But she learned how to muffle the bell
by stuffing a sock into it...

1239
02:06:54,064 --> 02:06:57,108
and inching her way out of the bed...

1240
02:06:57,192 --> 02:06:59,110
and into the night.

1241
02:07:00,321 --> 02:07:02,196
He caught her one night
when the sock fell out...

1242
02:07:02,281 --> 02:07:04,824
and he heard her trying to run to the highway.

1243
02:07:04,908 --> 02:07:07,577
He caught her,
dragged her back to the trailer...

1244
02:07:07,661 --> 02:07:10,705
and tied her to the stove with his belt.

1245
02:07:12,541 --> 02:07:17,211
He just left her there and went back to bed...

1246
02:07:17,296 --> 02:07:21,174
and lay there, listening to her scream.

1247
02:07:21,258 --> 02:07:25,511
Then he listened to his son scream.

1248
02:07:25,596 --> 02:07:28,097
He was surprised at himself because...

1249
02:07:28,182 --> 02:07:31,017
he didn't feel anything anymore.

1250
02:07:32,603 --> 02:07:35,605
All he wanted to do was sleep.

1251
02:07:37,524 --> 02:07:39,734
And for the first time...

1252
02:07:39,818 --> 02:07:42,612
he wished he were far away...

1253
02:07:45,741 --> 02:07:50,536
lost in a deep, vast country
where nobody knew him...

1254
02:07:50,621 --> 02:07:53,289
somewhere without language...

1255
02:07:53,374 --> 02:07:56,084
or streets.

1256
02:07:56,168 --> 02:08:00,171
And he dreamed about this place
without knowing its name.

1257
02:08:00,255 --> 02:08:03,591
And when he woke up, he was on fire.

1258
02:08:06,595 --> 02:08:10,556
There were blue flames
burning the sheets of his bed.

1259
02:08:10,641 --> 02:08:13,351
He ran through the flames...

1260
02:08:13,435 --> 02:08:16,938
toward the only two people he loved...

1261
02:08:17,022 --> 02:08:18,940
but they were gone.

1262
02:08:21,610 --> 02:08:25,613
His arms were burning,
and he threw himself outside and -

1263
02:08:27,282 --> 02:08:29,951
and rolled on the wet ground.

1264
02:08:32,204 --> 02:08:34,205
Then he ran.

1265
02:08:35,457 --> 02:08:37,959
He never looked back at the fire.

1266
02:08:40,462 --> 02:08:42,672
He just ran.

1267
02:08:48,554 --> 02:08:51,222
He ran until the sun came up...

1268
02:08:52,433 --> 02:08:55,560
and he couldn't run any further.

1269
02:08:56,729 --> 02:08:59,230
Then when the sun went down...

1270
02:08:59,314 --> 02:09:01,315
he ran again.

1271
02:09:07,156 --> 02:09:11,075
For five days, he ran like this...

1272
02:09:11,160 --> 02:09:14,036
until every sign of man...

1273
02:09:16,790 --> 02:09:18,791
had disappeared.

1274
02:09:29,845 --> 02:09:31,804
Travis.

1275
02:10:14,348 --> 02:10:17,600
If you turn the light off in there,
will you be able to see me?

1276
02:10:26,026 --> 02:10:28,027
I don't know.

1277
02:10:32,533 --> 02:10:34,534
I never tried.

1278
02:10:53,303 --> 02:10:55,471
Can you see me?

1279
02:10:56,974 --> 02:10:59,684
Yeah.

1280
02:10:59,768 --> 02:11:01,936
Do you recognize me?

1281
02:11:04,022 --> 02:11:05,940
Oh, Travis.

1282
02:11:13,407 --> 02:11:15,908
I brought Hunter with me.

1283
02:11:28,005 --> 02:11:30,339
Don't you want to see him?

1284
02:11:32,426 --> 02:11:34,343
Yeah.

1285
02:11:42,978 --> 02:11:47,523
I wanted to see him so bad
that I didn't even dare imagine him anymore.

1286
02:11:53,655 --> 02:11:56,490
Anne kept sendin' me pictures of him...

1287
02:11:59,453 --> 02:12:01,954
until I asked her to stop.

1288
02:12:08,170 --> 02:12:11,213
I couldn't stand the... pain...

1289
02:12:11,298 --> 02:12:14,300
of seeing him grow up and missin' it.

1290
02:12:23,185 --> 02:12:26,187
Why didn't you keep him with you, Jane?

1291
02:12:29,316 --> 02:12:31,317
I couldn't, Travis.

1292
02:12:35,447 --> 02:12:38,449
I didn't have what I knew he needed.

1293
02:12:45,082 --> 02:12:48,751
I didn't want to use him
to fill all my emptiness.

1294
02:12:54,132 --> 02:12:56,467
Well, he needs you now, Jane...

1295
02:12:56,551 --> 02:12:58,511
and he wants to see you.

1296
02:12:58,595 --> 02:13:00,596
He does?

1297
02:13:03,058 --> 02:13:04,976
Yes.

1298
02:13:09,106 --> 02:13:11,607
He's - He's waiting for you.

1299
02:13:11,692 --> 02:13:13,609
Where?

1300
02:13:16,113 --> 02:13:18,614
Downtown...

1301
02:13:18,699 --> 02:13:20,700
in a hotel.

1302
02:13:22,577 --> 02:13:24,495
The Meridian.

1303
02:13:26,456 --> 02:13:28,416
Room 1520.

1304
02:13:33,296 --> 02:13:35,256
1520.

1305
02:13:36,341 --> 02:13:39,176
You're not going, are you?

1306
02:13:53,859 --> 02:13:56,360
I can't see you, Jane.

1307
02:13:58,238 --> 02:14:06,238
Don't go yet.

1308
02:14:24,806 --> 02:14:26,766
I -

1309
02:14:28,977 --> 02:14:32,646
I used to make up long speeches to you
after you left.

1310
02:14:37,694 --> 02:14:40,404
I used to talk to you all the time...

1311
02:14:40,489 --> 02:14:42,823
even though I was alone.

1312
02:14:46,161 --> 02:14:49,663
I walked around for months talking to you.

1313
02:14:53,710 --> 02:14:56,212
Now I don't know what to say.

1314
02:15:00,801 --> 02:15:03,803
It was easier when I just imagined you.

1315
02:15:11,686 --> 02:15:14,688
I even imagined you talking back to me.

1316
02:15:19,319 --> 02:15:22,238
We'd have long conversations...

1317
02:15:23,782 --> 02:15:25,783
the two of us.

1318
02:15:29,412 --> 02:15:31,914
It was almost like you were there.

1319
02:15:36,211 --> 02:15:38,212
I could hear you.

1320
02:15:38,296 --> 02:15:40,297
I could see you, smell you.

1321
02:15:42,384 --> 02:15:44,385
I could hear your voice.

1322
02:15:47,389 --> 02:15:50,057
Sometimes your voice would wake me up.

1323
02:15:52,894 --> 02:15:54,895
It would wake me up in the middle of the night...

1324
02:15:54,980 --> 02:15:57,231
just like you were there in the room with me.

1325
02:16:05,740 --> 02:16:07,700
Then...

1326
02:16:10,537 --> 02:16:12,538
it slowly faded.

1327
02:16:14,624 --> 02:16:17,126
I couldn't picture you anymore.

1328
02:16:20,755 --> 02:16:24,008
I tried to talk out loud to you like I used to...

1329
02:16:24,092 --> 02:16:26,594
but there was nothin' there.

1330
02:16:29,973 --> 02:16:32,349
I couldn't hear you.

1331
02:16:37,606 --> 02:16:39,565
Then...

1332
02:16:44,404 --> 02:16:46,405
I just gave up.

1333
02:16:52,829 --> 02:16:54,997
Everything stopped.

1334
02:16:56,791 --> 02:16:58,709
You...

1335
02:17:02,464 --> 02:17:04,632
just disappeared.

1336
02:17:10,805 --> 02:17:13,057
Now I'm working here.

1337
02:17:18,605 --> 02:17:21,440
I hear your voice all the time.

1338
02:17:25,737 --> 02:17:29,657
Every man...

1339
02:17:29,741 --> 02:17:31,992
has your voice.

1340
02:17:50,679 --> 02:17:54,181
I'll tell Hunter... that you're coming.

1341
02:17:59,104 --> 02:18:01,689
- Travis?
- What?

1342
02:18:05,485 --> 02:18:07,486
I'll be there.

1343
02:18:12,158 --> 02:18:14,076
Good.

1344
02:18:19,040 --> 02:18:20,958
Meridian Hotel.

1345
02:18:21,042 --> 02:18:22,960
Yeah.

1346
02:18:26,548 --> 02:18:30,259
Room 1520.

1347
02:19:39,120 --> 02:19:41,872
Yeah!

1348
02:19:41,956 --> 02:19:44,708
"Why, you little" -

1349
02:19:44,793 --> 02:19:47,836
Yeah!

1350
02:19:47,921 --> 02:19:51,715
Yeah.

1351
02:21:19,679 --> 02:21:22,181
Your hair, it's wet.

1352
02:21:31,232 --> 02:21:33,484
Oh!